//Fracture â€“ Clavicle

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Shoulder MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Fracture' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Proximal humerus' radio button is enabled
And 'Clavicle' radio button is enabled
And 'Scapula' radio button is enabled
And 'Humeral diaphysis' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Clavicle' radio button
Then '15A: Clavicle, sternal end' radio button is enabled
And '15B: Clavicle, body' radio button is enabled
And '15C: Clavicle, acromial end' radio button is enabled
And '15: Not further specified' radio button is enabled
And 'Serial number' input field is enabled
And 'Image number' input field is enabled
And 'Import reference image' image uploader field is enabled


When I select '15A: Clavicle, sternal end' radio button
Then 'Extraarticular fx with epiphyseal injury' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial articular' radio button is enabled
And 'Articular fracture' radio button is enabled

When I select '15B: Clavicle, body'
Then 'Simple fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Wedge fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Multifragmentary fracture' radio button is enabled

When I select '15C: Clavicle, acromial end'
Then 'Extraarticular' radio button is enabled
And 'Intraarticular' radio button is enabled

When I select '15: Not further specified'
Then 'Remodelling' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspected' radio button is enabled
